Goal The video player requires subtitles in WebVTT format (.vtt). Because admins can upload .srt subtitles, the system uses Lambda netflop-subtitle-converter to automatically convert .srt files to .vtt.
Subtitle processing flow Admin upload .srt | v S3 input subtitle-input/ | v Lambda netflop-subtitle-converter | v S3 output subtitles/*.vtt | v Backend stores subtitle URL | v Video Player displays subtitle track Upload handling File type Handling .vtt Uploaded directly to S3 output and saved in database .srt Uploaded to S3 input, Lambda converts it to .vtt, then the backend/player uses the .vtt file S3 trigger Lambda is triggered by new objects:
Bucket: netflop-input-source Prefix: subtitle-input/ Suffix: .srt Event: s3:ObjectCreated:* Admin UI notes The admin interface should clearly display:
The episode associated with the subtitle. Subtitle language, e.g. Vietnamese. Whether the uploaded file is .srt or .vtt. Conversion status when uploading .srt. The final .vtt URL after conversion. Verification Upload an .srt file from the admin panel. Confirm the file appears under netflop-input-source/subtitle-input/. Check CloudWatch Logs for Lambda netflop-subtitle-converter. Confirm a .vtt file is created in the S3 output bucket. Open the video player and enable subtitles. Verify that subtitles display correctly without duplicate lines on mobile. How subtitle upload and conversion works When the admin uploads subtitles:
If the file is .vtt, the backend uploads it directly to S3 output. If the file is .srt, the backend uploads the source to S3 input with metadata for the output bucket/key. The backend may also convert SRT to VTT immediately to return a URL to the web UI. The netflop-subtitle-converter Lambda still processes .srt objects created under subtitle-input/. Sample backend code for receiving SRT if (isSubtitle &amp;&amp; extension === &#39;.srt&#39;) { const { inputKey, outputKey } = subtitleObjectKeys(body, req.file.originalname); const uploadedSource = await awsS3Service.uploadSubtitleSource(req.file, { inputKey, outputBucket: awsConfig.s3OutputBucket, outputKey, metadata }); const vttText = convertSrtBufferToVtt(req.file.buffer); const uploadedVtt = await awsS3Service.uploadPublicObject({ key: outputKey, body: Buffer.from(vttText, &#39;utf8&#39;), contentType: &#39;text/vtt; charset=utf-8&#39; }); } Sample Lambda SRT-to-VTT code function srtToWebVtt(srtText) { const body = String(srtText || &#39;&#39;) .replace(/
